I'm still beating myself up though because I have often left so many days between each session. The beginning went so well and now life gets in the way all the time. It doesn't fair very well for my discipline and self love if I can't even stick to 31 days. It's the same with my weight. It's crept up to 260lbs and I go and lose 10 then put it back on. Where is the switch?

AT the start of the video Adriene said about being in the NOW, and prior to tuning in to day 12, I was thinking ahead to what I want to do next year when it comes to my health and wellbeing.  Whilee I was moving through today's class it occurred to me, not to start next year, but start today.  Instead of thinking to next year or even next week, if you have got plans to up your health and wellbeing, do it NOW not later, and so from today's class it wasn't just about my health and wellbeing but about pulling my life together NOW.  It is amazing what thoughts flow through your mind when you are focused on your breathing and yourself for 30 minutes and at the same time, tuned into one voice around you.

I really pushed to make today's session happen for me in the morning as I had a list of things I have to do for the day, and I made it a priority to put Adriene at the top of my list of what I need to do.  Knowing that I am more capable of doing yoga in the morning compared to the afternoon or evening, I have made the commitment to do the revolution in the morning or as early as possible if there is an appointment to be had.  I am committed to pushing myself through this routine of yoga in the morning and then walking in the day.  

I am still waking up feeling tired and by the mid afternoon I am starting to wind down but I am wanting to add extra exercise into my routine.  I will stay with the yoga until I am able to fully commit to another exercise.  Spiritually, I feel as though I am ready, but physically I have a long way to go.  It has only been 2 weeks since turning into Adriene and I am in a good place, as I am focused on what is important to me NOW and it is finding movement in my day through yoga and through walking and concentrate on what I can do NOW and not what I want to do.

Thank you Adriene for inviting us to all of your practices. My friends and I started the " 30 days of Yoga " because we had done it in the pass and saw the benefits of it, but just couldn't find the right instructor, until now.  A quick back story of how we got here. We are all rock climbers and it was hard to progress each and every time we showed up to the gym, some of us had plateaued and didn't know how to get out of our funk. How can we become stronger, flexible, and tone?  It was a lot of fun!  It was kind of like a book club, we would usually talk about how we enjoyed some days and some days you kicked our butts.  We started noticing a change after the first day. Not only in our climbing lives, but our overall life style. How we move, breath, and speak all changed as we kept on knocking out the days.  

In the beginning my goal was to get more fit for rock climbing, but now my goal is to be a better human being not only to others but to myself as well. Words cannot express how grateful I am to you and this community for showing my friends and I how to not only get stronger physically but mentally as well. Thank you for showing us the vault of emotions and strength that was hidden inside all of us.
